; pnpm hoist configuration for the iogrid monorepo.
;
; The repo intentionally hosts two React majors side-by-side:
;   - web/         pins react@18.3.1 + @types/react@18.3.x   (production app)
;   - marketing/   pins react@19.0.0-rc + @types/react@19.x   (RC trial)
;
; Default pnpm behaviour public-hoists `@types/*` into
; `node_modules/.pnpm/node_modules/`. With two `@types/react` versions
; in play, pnpm picks ONE to hoist (typically the newest, 19.0.1), and
; that becomes the version tsc resolves when walking up from packages
; that have no explicit @types/react peer pin (next/dist/styled-jsx,
; next-auth, next/link). The result: web's tsc sees a `React.ReactNode`
; that includes `bigint` (the 19.x addition) while web's own JSX uses
; @types/react@18.3.12 (no bigint) -> dual `ReactNode` types -> every
; forwardRef component (Link, Button, Input) fails TS2786.
;
; Excluding @types/react + @types/react-dom from BOTH the public hoist
; (root node_modules/) and the internal hoist (node_modules/.pnpm/
; node_modules/) forces each workspace's own pin to be the only
; resolution. The internal hoist is what was triggering tsc's
; React.ReactNode bigint mismatch in the web workspace.
public-hoist-pattern[]=*types*
public-hoist-pattern[]=*eslint*
public-hoist-pattern[]=!@types/react
public-hoist-pattern[]=!@types/react-dom
hoist-pattern[]=*
hoist-pattern[]=!@types/react
hoist-pattern[]=!@types/react-dom
